    {
      "text": "Rapid Racer, known as Turbo Prop Racing in North America, is a racing video game developed and published by Sony Computer Entertainment for the PlayStation. In the game, the player takes control of a motorboat and races around six different tracks. Eventually, all six tracks can be raced in mirrored mode, as well as at night.\nBy winning championships and completing bonus rounds (unlocked by collecting five yellow icons during a race on the first two-day tracks), players can unlock rewards, which they can use either to upgrade their boat or to unlock a higher-powered one.",
